 .IR version ]
@@ -80,6 +84,12 @@ switch. In this case only one rpm has to be specified. An identity
 deltarpm can be useful to just replace the signature header of a
 rpm or to reconstruct a rpm from the filesystem.
 
+Specifying
+.B -l
+.IR file,
+one can give a file with a list of files needed to be excluded from the delta process. Nowadays it is relayed on all of those files be either
+marked as %config or as %verify(nomd5) in spec files. Thus, this option is obsolete.
